.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-module-trust - Trust a module source (owner/repo, owner/*, or a host), or list trusted sources with --list


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel module trust [pattern] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Trust a module source (owner/repo, owner/*, or a host), or list trusted sources with --list


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for trust

.PP
\fB--identity\fP=""
	Expected keyless cosign signing identity (e.g. an email or GitHub Actions workflow URI).

.PP
\fB--issuer\fP=""
	Expected keyless cosign OIDC issuer (e.g. https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com). Used with --identity.

.PP
\fB--key\fP=""
	Path/URL/KMS URI to a cosign public key for keyful signature verification.

.PP
\fB--list\fP[=false]
	List the trusted-source patterns instead of adding one.

.PP
\fB--require-signature\fP[=false]
	Mark this source as a verified publisher and require a valid cosign image signature at install time.


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-module(1)\fP
